{"source_key":"sha256-852da461b9759bc2736926d9891eb9a3","record_index":10095,"record_hash":"sha256:cbbac7ecc461a311a3c0b18623e311c9dfd0e3616aebfa91b709a6533e47c3fc","timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:46:58.280Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"I ran six agent-consumer simulations and updated [handoff-design.md](</Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 [REDACTED:entropy].md>).\n\nThe pattern was pretty clear: keep the three tools, but make the outputs smarter.\n\n```text\nbut agentlog sessions [branch [<branch>] | review <review> | change <change>] [--limit N]\nbut agentlog timeline <session-key> [--limit N]\nbut agentlog records <session-key> --turn <turn-key> [--from start|end|<index>] [--limit N]\n```\n\nWhat changed from the simulation:\n\n- `sessions branch` with no branch name should mean current branch.\n- `sessions` needs match evidence: why did this session match, which turns matched, what other targets were observed. No fake confidence score.\n- `timeline` needs to be a triage surface: stable turn index, record counts, coverage metadata, observed targets, tiny user/assistant previews, maybe tool/command counts.\n- `records` should default to `--from end`, return records in natural order within that window, and include stable range metadata for paging backward.\n- No filtering in v1. Clear record kinds are enough; filters/search can come later if real usage hurts.\n- No `handoff`, no `show`, no `--interesting`, no auto-main-session selection. Tempting, but they hide policy.\n\nThe most useful framing: the receiving agent navigates by **session -> turn -> records**, not record-by-record. The turn is the unit of orientation; records are the source of truth once a turn looks relevant.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:46:58.280Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}